(52, 'Barbara Bridges, Esq.', 'Barbara', 'Bridges, Esq.', 'Weill, Gotshal & Manges LLP', '6', 'barb.jpg', '', '', '', '', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Bookman Old Style&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri">Barbara Bridges is a Capital\nMarkets Associates at Weil, Gotshal &amp; Magnes, one of the largest law firms\nin the country. Their practice areas range from business restructuring to\nexecutive compensation. The firm employs over 1,200 lawyers and has gross\nannual revenue that excess of $1.1 Billion.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Bookman Old Style&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\nArial"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Bookman Old Style&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\nArial">During her time at Weil, Ms. Bridges also worked as a secondment with\nGoldman Sachs as a compliance officer, where she r</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Bookman Old Style&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">esearched\nclient accounts to ensure their compliance with anti-money laundering/know your\nclient laws.</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\n&quot;Bookman Old Style&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Bookman Old Style&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\nArial"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Bookman Old Style&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\nArial">Prior to joining Weil, Ms. Bridges worked at Oxfam America as a policy\nintern, where shed d</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;\nfont-family:&quot;Bookman Old Style&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">rafted policy recommendations\nconcerning issuing affecting the Gulf Coast as well as farmer’s workers rights\nto be considered by Congress.&nbsp; &nbsp;Barbara previously worked at New York\nUniversity Medical Center in the Legal Department. </span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Bookman Old Style&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Arial"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;\nline-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Bookman Old Style&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\nArial"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n<span style="font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Bookman Old Style&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\nmso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;mso-ansi-language:\nEN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA">Barbara received a\nB.A. from the Emory University, where he studied political science and English,\nand she received a J.D. from Columbia Law Schools. During law school, she was\nan Editor-in-chief of the National Black Law Journal.</span>', NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, '1', NULL),
